data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[kə'neəri]
*danh từ
 ■chim hoàng yến ((cũng) canary bird)
 ■rượu vang canari ((cũng) canary wine)
◘[canary]
saying && slang
 ■a person who tells the police, a squealer
 ⁃Ken - that canary! He tells the boss who comes in late.

Anh - Anh
canary
■ noun (plural canaries)
1》 a bright yellow finch with a melodious song, popular as a cage bird. [Serinus canaria (Canary Islands, Azores, and Madeira) and related species in Africa.]
2》 (also canary yellow) a bright yellow colour.
3》 historical a sweet wine from the Canary Islands, similar to Madeira.
Origin
C16: from Fr. canari, from Sp. canario 'canary' or 'person from the Canary Islands'.

Kết hợp từ & Cấu trúc câu
canary
n. a canary sings
